
  Usage: heimlich config <plugins ...> [options]

  Writes the default config of selected plugins
  to the ./config directory.

  plugins is an optionally empty list of plugin
  names for which to write the config files. If
  the list is empty, the config files for all
  plugins are written.

  The list of available plugins is:

    - heimlich
    - css
    - modernizr
    - uglify

  Options:

    --format fmt    the output format (yaml, js or json)
                    defaults to yaml.

    --overwrite     allow overwriting of existing files
                    defaults to not overwriting

  Example: write the css.yaml config file to ./config:

    heimlich config css
